<heading id="D09C0F52FF02FF30427D10E73FAC0E7B" box="[594,993,511,538]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" reason="2">
<emphasis id="B91F642CFF02FF30427D10E73FAC0E7B" bold="true" box="[594,993,511,538]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">
Species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BC3BDFF02FF30432C10E73FC20E78" authorityName="de Saussure" authorityYear="1890" box="[771,911,511,538]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Sphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malagassus">
<emphasis id="B91F642CFF02FF30432C10E73FC20E78" bold="true" box="[771,911,511,538]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">malagassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C371EBB5FF02FF30409213583E380FD7" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD4B83EFF02FF3040921358393B0E39" blockId="147.[189,1398,576,603]" box="[189,1398,576,603]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">
The 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BC3BDFF02FF3040DF13583D340E38" authorityName="de Saussure" authorityYear="1890" box="[240,377,576,602]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Sphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malagassus">
<emphasis id="B91F642CFF02FF3040DF13583D340E38" box="[240,377,576,602]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">malagassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group contains the following two species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BC3BDFF02FF30434A135838780E38" authority="Dörfel &amp; Ohl, 2022" authorityName="Dörfel &amp; Ohl" authorityYear="2022" box="[869,1077,576,602]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Sphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="comorensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B91F642CFF02FF30434A135838780E38" box="[869,1077,576,602]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">Sphex comorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22CD957FF02FF304413135938D80E39" box="[1084,1173,577,603]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BC3BDFF02FF3044E6135939230E38" authorityName="de Saussure" authorityYear="1890" box="[1225,1390,576,603]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Sphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malagassus">
<emphasis id="B91F642CFF02FF3044E6135939230E38" box="[1225,1390,576,603]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">S. malagassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD4B83EFF02FF304092139A3E380FD7" blockId="147.[188,1399,642,950]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">
The species in this group possess perpendicularly-oriented erect propodeal setae, and the scutellar vestiture is somewhat dense and can be fine or coarse. Therefore, members can be superficially similar to those of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BC3BDFF02FF30415E13D03E490E80" authorityName="Ruspolia" baseAuthorityName="Arnold" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[369,516,712,738]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Sphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis id="B91F642CFF02FF30415E13D03E490E80" box="[369,516,712,738]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BC3BDFF02FF30426513D03EF10E80" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1916" box="[586,700,712,738]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Sphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umtalicus">
<emphasis id="B91F642CFF02FF30426513D03EF10E80" box="[586,700,712,738]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">umtalicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups. What reliably separates them from these groups is the fact that their metanotum is not raised at all, whereas members of the other two groups normally have it somewhat elevated towards its center, although without the distinct tubercles which are present in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BC3BDFF02FF304092122B3D740F2E" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1787" box="[189,313,819,844]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Sphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentatus">
<emphasis id="B91F642CFF02FF304092122B3D740F2E" box="[189,313,819,844]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">argentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. In the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BC3BDFF02FF3041F1122A3E2A0F2E" authorityName="de Saussure" authorityYear="1890" box="[478,615,818,844]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Sphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malagassus">
<emphasis id="B91F642CFF02FF3041F1122A3E2A0F2E" box="[478,615,818,844]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">malagassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, the erect propodeal setae are straight instead of curved, and the wings are no more than slightly infuscate. Finally, both species are only known from 
<collectingCountry id="F37CF8AEFF02FF3044C6124D393A0F0D" box="[1257,1399,853,879]" name="Madagascar" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
or the surrounding islands, repectively, whereas the members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BC3BDFF02FF3043CE126038380FF0" authorityName="Ruspolia" baseAuthorityName="Arnold" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[993,1141,888,914]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Sphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis id="B91F642CFF02FF3043CE126038380FF0" box="[993,1141,888,914]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6BC3BDFF02FF304496126039660FF0" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1916" box="[1209,1323,888,914]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Sphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umtalicus">
<emphasis id="B91F642CFF02FF304496126039660FF0" box="[1209,1323,888,914]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">umtalicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group seem to be restricted to the mainland.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
